@startuml arquitectura-1.deployment
title Arquitectura 1 - SPA estática + BFF + IdP corporativo (OAuth 2.0/OIDC)

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 150
skinparam ranksep 150

actor "Usuario" as User

node "Navegador" as Browser {
  component "SPA estática" as SPA
  artifact "Cookie SESSION_ID\n(HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite)" as Cookie
}

cloud "CDN / Hosting estático" as CDN {
  artifact "index.html / JS / CSS" as StaticFiles
}

node "Zona aplicación (servidor)" as AppZone {
  component "BFF - Cliente OAuth2/OIDC\n[genera code_verifier, code_challenge]" as BFF
  database "Store de sesión y tokens\n[tokens NUNCA llegan al navegador]" as SessionStore
}

node "Plataforma IAM corporativa" as IAM {
  component "Authorization Server / IdP\n[valida code_challenge con SHA-256]" as AS
  database "Directorio corporativo" as Directory
  artifact "JWKS\n[claves públicas de firma]" as JWKS
}

node "Zona APIs" as APIZone {
  component "Resource Server\nAPI protegida" as API
}

node "Observabilidad" as OBS {
  component "Logs / SIEM" as SIEM
}

User -[hidden]down-> Browser
Browser -[hidden]down-> BFF
BFF -[hidden]down-> AS
AS -[hidden]down-> API
API -[hidden]down-> SIEM

User --> Browser
Browser --> CDN : GET SPA
CDN --> Browser : Archivos estáticos

Browser --> BFF : HTTPS + Cookie SESSION_ID
BFF --> AS : /authorize\nclient_id + challenge (S256) + state + nonce
AS --> Directory : autenticar usuario / MFA
AS --> Browser : callback: code + state
Browser --> BFF : /callback?code=...&state=...
BFF --> BFF : validar state/nonce
BFF --> AS : POST /token\ncode + code_verifier
AS --> BFF : access_token + id_token (+ refresh_token)
BFF --> SessionStore : custodiar tokens server-side
BFF --> Browser : Set-Cookie SESSION_ID (sin tokens)
BFF --> API : Authorization: Bearer access_token
API --> JWKS : validar firma JWT / claves
API --> BFF : respuesta JSON
AS --> SIEM : log autenticación y emisión de token
BFF --> SIEM : log sesión y consumo API
API --> SIEM : log autorización backend

note right of SPA
La SPA NO guarda tokens.
Solo usa cookie de sesión contra el BFF.
OAuth 2.0/OIDC ocurre entre el BFF y el IdP.
end note

note right of BFF
PKCE S256:
  code_verifier = random seguro (≥43 chars)
  code_challenge = BASE64URL(SHA256(verifier))
El BFF envía challenge en /authorize
y verifier en /token.
end note

note right of AS
Validación PKCE del IdP/AS:
SHA256(code_verifier) == code_challenge
Si no coincide, rechaza el token exchange.
end note

note right of API
Validar en CADA solicitud:
  issuer, audience, exp, scopes.
No confiar solo en el Gateway.
end note

@enduml